    "text": "gy configurations operates accord-\ning to distinct update rules:gy configurations operates accord-\ning to distinct update rules:(1) Star-Star. Each group g initializes its model as x(r)\ng,0 = x(r). Within each group, clients initialize\ntheir models as x(r)\ng,p,m,0 = x(r)\ng,p, perform K parallel local updates, and send updates to the group\nserver for aggregation. After P group updates, the global server aggregates group parameters to\ngenerate the next global parameters x(r+1).\n(2) Star-Ring. Each group g initializes its model as x(r)\ng,0 = x(r). Within each group, clients initialize",
    "source": "iclr_2026.pdf",
    "page": 4,
    "chunk_id": 3
  },
