    "text": "Published as a conference paper at ICLR 2026\nA\nDISCUSSION\nA.1\nALGORITHM DETAILS\nFor clarity and completeness, this appendix provides the detailed pseudocode for the four HFL\ntopologies mentioned in the main body of our paper. Each algorithm outlines a different communi-\ncation pattern for both inter-group and intra-group model aggregation.\nThe Star-Star topology (Algorithm 1) represents a fully parallel framework. Both the groups at",
    "source": "iclr_2026.pdf",
    "page": 13,
    "chunk_id": 0
  },
  {
    "text": "thm 1) represents a fully parallel framework. Both the groups atthm 1) represents a fully parallel framework. Both the groups atthe server level and the clients within each group perform their training and updates in parallel,\nsynchronizing with their respective servers before aggregation.\nAlgorithm 1 Star-Star Hierarchical FL\n1: for global rounds r = 0, 1, . . . , R ‚àí1 do\n2:\nfor groups g = 1, 2, . . . , G in parallel do\n3:\nInitialize group model: x(r)\ng,0 = x(r)\n4:\nfor group rounds p = 0, 1, . . . , P ‚àí1 do\n5:\nfor clients m = 1, 2, . . . , M in parallel do\n6:\nInitialize local model: x(r)\ng,p,m,0 = x(r)\ng,p\n7:",
    "source": "iclr_2026.pdf",
    "page": 13,
    "chunk_id": 1
  },
  {
    "text": "arallel do\n6:\nInitialize local model: x(r)\ng,p,m,0 = x(r)\ng,p\n7:arallel do\n6:\nInitialize local model: x(r)\ng,p,m,0 = x(r)\ng,p\n7:for local steps k = 0, 1, . . . , K ‚àí1 do\n8:\nx(r)\ng,p,m,k+1 = x(r)\ng,p,m,k ‚àíŒ∑g(r)\ng,p,m,k\n9:\nend for\n10:\nend for\n11:\nGroup aggregation: x(r)\ng,p+1 =\n1\nM\nPM\nm=1 x(r)\ng,p,m,K\n12:\nend for\n13:\nend for\n14:\nGlobal aggregation: x(r+1) = 1\nG\nPG\ng=1 x(r)\ng,P\n15: end for\nThe Star-Ring topology (Algorithm 2) combines parallel inter-group communication with sequential\nintra-group updates. While groups update in parallel with the global server, clients within each group",
    "source": "iclr_2026.pdf",
    "page": 13,
    "chunk_id": 2
  },
  {
    "text": "te in parallel with the global server, clients within each groupte in parallel with the global server, clients within each groupform a ring, passing the model sequentially from one client to the next.\nAlgorithm 2 Star-Ring Hierarchical FL\n1: for global rounds r = 0, 1, . . . , R ‚àí1 do\n2:\nfor groups g = 1, 2, . . . , G in parallel do\n3:\nInitialize group model: x(r)\ng,0 = x(r)\n4:\nfor group rounds p = 0, 1, . . . , P ‚àí1 do\n5:\nfor clients m = 1, 2, . . . , M in sequence do\n6:\nInitialize local model: x(r)\ng,p,m,0 =\n(\nx(r)\ng,p\nif m = 1\nx(r)\ng,p,m‚àí1,K\nif m > 1\n7:\nfor local steps k = 0, 1, . . . , K ‚àí1 do\n8:\nx(r)\ng,p,m,k+1 = x(r)",
    "source": "iclr_2026.pdf",
    "page": 13,
    "chunk_id": 3
  },
  {
