    "text": "odel: x(r+1) = x(r)\nG,P\n15: end for\nA.2\nWALL-CLOCK TIME ANALYSISodel: x(r+1) = x(r)\nG,P\n15: end for\nA.2\nWALL-CLOCK TIME ANALYSISTo bridge the gap between convergence rounds and real-world training latency, we analyze the total\nwall-clock time T. This is defined as the sum of computation and communication overheads: T =\nTComp + TComm. Let S denote the model size, œÑx the computation time for a node x, and rA‚ÜíB the\ntransmission rate from node A to B.\nSingle-Layer Analysis. In a single-layer setting with M clients, the Star topology is limited by\nthe straggler, i.e., T Star = maxm{\nS\nr0‚Üím + œÑm +\nS",
