    "text": "Published as a conference paper at ICLR 2026\nP\nm œÑm + PM\nm=2\nS\nrm‚àí1‚Üím +\nS\nrM‚Üí0 . While T Star theoretically offers O(1) communication scaling\nversus T Ring‚Äôs O(M), this assumes unlimited bandwidth, which rarely holds in edge scenarios.\nHFL Topology Analysis. The total wall-clock time for HFL over R global rounds, with P group\nrounds, can be unified as:\nTtotal = R ¬∑ (Tinter + P ¬∑ Tintra) ,\n(24)\nwhere Tinter represents the wall-clock time for inter-group updates, and Tintra represents the wall-",
